President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. The nominations include Craig B. Allen as Ambassador to Brunei Darussalam, Sharon Block as Member of the National Labor Relations Board, Richard M. Mills, Jr. as Ambassador to the Republic of Armenia, Joseph Nimmich as Deputy Administrator of the Federal Emergency Management Agency, Anne E. Rung as Administrator for Federal Procurement Policy, Alissa M. Starzak as General Counsel of the Army, and John Francis Tefft as Ambassador to the Russian Federation. The President also announced his intent to appoint Charles Benton as Member of the National Museum and Library Services Board, Robert Langer as Member of the President's Committee on the National Medal of Science, Lillian M. Lowery as Member of the President's Advisory Council on Financial Capability for Young Americans, Anne Ashmore-Hudson as Member of the Advisory Committee on the Arts for the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts, Steven M. Goldman as Member of the Advisory Committee on the Arts for the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts, Dale LeFebvre as Member of the Advisory Committee on the Arts for the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts, and Anita Lin as Member of the Advisory Committee on the Arts for the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts.